# Engine (`engine/`)

- **Entry:** `engine/main.py` — `traffic`, `revenue`, `full` orchestration.
- **Config load order (`engine/config.py`):**  
  `engine/.env` → repo `.env` → `web/.env.local` (**`load_dotenv(..., override=False)`** — first file wins per variable.)  
  Put secrets in **`web/.env.local`** only when you intentionally share them across web + engine.
- **LLM:**
  - **`ENGINE_USE_GROQ_ONLY`** or **`ENGINE_FORCE_GROQ`** → skip Gemini (**requires `GROQ_API_KEY`**). Use when Gemini free tier shows **`limit: 0`** / **429**.
  - Gemini retry: on quota-style errors → one Groq rerun; must clear **`agent.agent_executor`** after failed kickoff — see `engine/agents/orchestrator.py`.
- **Clarity:** **`CLARITY_API_TOKEN`** (Data Export API). **401/403** = bad/missing token.
- **Stripe decrypt:** **`STRIPE_SECRET_ENCRYPTION_KEY`** must match `web/` when reading encrypted Stripe columns.

Operational doc: **`docs/runbook-local.md`**.

Official references:

- CrewAI docs — https://docs.crewai.com/
- Google AI rate limits — https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/rate-limits
- Clarity Data Export API — https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/clarity/setup-and-installation/clarity-data-export-api
